<meta content='The secret lives of paintings' itemprop='name'>
<meta content='Art history is far from set in stone. Engineer Maurizio Seracini spent 30 years searching for Leonardo da Vinci&#x0027;s lost fresco "The Battle of Anghiari," and in the process discovered that many paintings have layers of history hidden underneath. Should they be part of the viewing experience too?' itemprop='description'>
